<p><a href="https://github.com/junjizhi/aide.el">aide.el</a> now supports calling <a href="https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/chat">OpenAI chat API endpoint</a>, which uses   <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gpt-3.5-turbo</code> model by default.</p>

<p>I implemented that in the new <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">aide-openai-chat</code> function.</p>

<p>You can highlight a region and send it to Chat API and let OpenAI finish the rest. Like previously implemented, Emacs will highlight the response.</p>

<p>Check out the demo:</p>

